Stanley Cup, only to leave as a free agent three years later, will rejoin the
team for next season. The Rangers scheduled a news conference Thursday morning
to announce the deal that will reportedly pay the 39-year-old center between $10
million to $11 million for two years. In his third season in New York, Messier
led the Rangers to their first championship in 54 years. He also won five titles
with the Oilers.
</P>
