<HEADLINE> FBI says Paterson man may be linked to string of bank robberies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CLIFTON, N.J. (AP) - A Paterson man charged in Wednesday's
robbery of a Clifton bank may be responsible for a string of North
Jersey bank robberies, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Sheppard, 46, was arrested minutes after the robbery at
the Clifton Savings Bank on Valley Road. Authorities say $1,830 in
cash was taken during the robbery.
</P>
<P>
   Sandra Carroll, an FBI spokeswoman, said Sheppard will be
arraigned in U.S. District Court in Newark on Thursday on charges
related to the Clifton robbery and robberies at the Dime Savings
Bank in Paterson on April 17 and Fleet Bank in Fair Lawn on June
22.
</P>
<P>
   Police and FBI officials are probing if Sheppard was involved in
the recent robberies of the First Union Bank in Paterson and the
Clifton Savings Bank in the city's Botany Village section.
</P>
</TEXT>
