   '20/20': Correspondent John Stossel reports on the case against
former doctor Michael Swango on tonight's edition of ''20/20.''
Swango, a doctor who lost his license after poisoning six
co-workers in the 1980s, was charged this week with killing three
patients at a veteran's hospital in Garden City, N.Y. Also: Why did
an 81-year-old Florida widow spend more than $100,000 on dance
lessons at Dance Tonight studios? Correspondent Arnold Diaz speaks
