<HEADLINE> AP Corrects AIDS Conference Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DURBAN, South Africa (AP) -- In a July 8 story, The Associated
Press erroneously reported that the U.S. Centers for Disease
Control and Prevention had concluded that 2 percent to 4 percent of
adult Americans have sex or drug habits that put them at high risk
of catching the AIDS virus. The figures should have been 2 percent
to 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The error resulted from a miscalculation by the CDC.
</P>
