<HEADLINE> Rosie O'Donnell Moving to N.Y.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   VALLEY COTTAGE, N.Y. (AP) -- Rosie O'Donnell is moving back to
Rockland County.
</P>
<P>
   The talk show host, comedian and actress is buying a hilltop
home in Valley Cottage, not far from the Nyack house she left in
December, publicist Lois Smith said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''She never wanted to leave Rockland in the first place,'' Smith
said. ''She's thrilled to be coming back.''
</P>
<P>
   O'Donnell and her three children moved away because of fears
that her Nyack house, once owned by Helen Hayes, was too close to a
main street to offer enough privacy and security.
</P>
<P>
   She moved to Greenwich, Conn., and caused an uproar there when a
bodyguard hired to protect her oldest son applied for a
concealed-weapon permit. O'Donnell advocates gun control, and
National Rifle Association officials and others accused her of
hypocrisy.
</P>
</TEXT>
