<HEADLINE> Nurse's aide gets up to 50 years for raping elderly woman  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WAMPSVILLE, N.Y. (AP) - A former nurse's aide was sentenced to
between 25 years and 50 years in prison Thursday for repeatedly
raping a 92-year-old patient at a Madison County nursing home.
</P>
<P>
   Arthur Wallace, 42, of Sherburne was arrested in February and
charged with sexually assaulting the woman five times in September
and October 1997 while a nurse's aide at the Oneida City Hospital
Extended Care Facility.
</P>
<P>
   Wallace was found guilty of five counts of first-degree rape in
May, and sentenced to two consecutive terms of 12&AMP;frac12; years to 25
years in prison Thursday by Madison County Court Judge Hugh
Humphreys. He was also sentenced to three concurrent 12&AMP;frac12;
year-to-25-year terms.
</P>
<P>
   Wallace had been fired at the Oneida health care facility in
September 1998 for sexually harassing fellow employees.
</P>
<P>
   According to state Attorney General Eliot Spitzer, Wallace had
been court-martialed from the U.S. Army prior to working in Oneida
for having lewd and lascivious contact with a minor. He failed to
note in his application in Oneida that he had any prior criminal
convictions, Spitzer said.
</P>
</TEXT>
