<HEADLINE> Democrat seeks Senate primary against Clinton  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - Democratic U.S. Senate candidate Mark S.
McMahon filed more than 40,000 petition signatures with the state
Board of Elections Thursday, potentially forcing a primary against
Democratic front-runner Hillary Rodham Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   The signatures must be verified by the board of elections before
placing the Manhattan doctor's name on a Sept. 12 primary ballot.
</P>
