<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-13 20:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Media General announces sale of several newspapers, newsprint company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   RICHMOND, Va. (AP) - Media General Inc., publisher of the
Richmond Times-Dispatch, said Thursday it will sell a group of
Virginia and North Carolina newspapers to Boone Newspapers Inc. of
Tuscaloosa, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   The sale involves the daily Suffolk, Va., News-Herald, the
tri-weekly Roanoke-Chowan News-Herald in Ahoskie, N.C., and several
smaller publications. The terms of the deal were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   H. Graham Woodlief Jr., president of Media General's publishing
division, said the papers being sold are isolated from the
company's larger properties and will make a better strategic fit
with Boone Newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   James B. Boone Jr., chairman of Boone Newspapers, was publisher
of the Suffolk paper in the 1960s.
</P>
<P>
   Media General also announced plans to sell its Garden State
Paper Co., a recycled newsprint manufacturer, for $72 million to an
affiliate of Enron North America Corp.
</P>
<P>
   The Garden State sale is expected to close in the third quarter.
Media General has owned the Garfield, N.J., mill for more than 30
years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
