<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man kills dying wife, self  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ACRA, N.Y. (AP) - Police believe an 80-year-old man shot his
dying, 93-year-old wife then killed himself late Wednesday or early
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The bodies of Michael and Agnes Fromm were found in bed by a
neighbor making a daily check on the couple in their home in this
hamlet 28 miles southwest of Albany.
</P>
<P>
   State police Senior Investigator David Darling said it appears
Michael Fromm shot his wife, who was dying of colon cancer, three
times in the chest before using the unlicensed, .32-caliber
revolver to kill himself.
</P>
<P>
   Darling told the Kingston Daily Freeman that police believe Mrs.
Fromm was suffering badly in the hours leading up to the shooting.
Mr. Fromm was her primary provider though she had been receiving
hospice care since June.
</P>
<P>
   The couple retired to Acra in Greene County in the late 1970s
after living in the Bronx.
</P>
<P>
   Darling said Michael Fromm also was ill, suffering from heart
disease. He had told neighbors he could not live without his wife.
</P>
<P>
   The couple had no children.
</P>
</TEXT>
