<HEADLINE> Braves 6, Orioles 3  </HEADLINE>
By DAVID GINSBURG
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE (AP) -- Greg Maddux outpitched Mike Mussina and Bobby
Bonilla singled in the tiebreaking run in the seventh inning as the
Atlanta Braves beat Baltimore 6-3 Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Maddux (11-3) allowed three runs, eight hits and two walks in
seven innings to earn his second consecutive win after two straight
defeats. It was his first appearance since July 4 due to a shoulder
injury that forced the right-hander to miss one start and skip the
All-Star game.
</P>
<P>
   Mussina (6-8) yielded only six hits in his third complete game,
struck out eight and retired the side in order six times. But the
Braves scored three runs in the fourth, snapped a 3-3 tie in the
seventh and added two insurance runs in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   John Rocker, greeted by a chorus of boos from the sellout crowd
of 47,284, started the ninth but walked Will Clark on four pitches.
Scott Kamieniecki finished for his first save of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Andres Galarraga led off the seventh with a single and took
second on a groundout before Bonilla grounded a soft single to
right. Bonilla, a former Oriole, had struck out in his previous two
at-bats against Mussina and was batting .229 against right-handed
pitching.
</P>
<P>
   Reggie Sanders, who entered as a pinch-runner for Bonilla,
singled in a run in the ninth and scored on a squeeze bunt by Walt
Weiss.
</P>
<P>
   The Orioles scored in the second when Clark hit a two-out single
and Harold Baines followed with an RBI double.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta's first nine batters were retired before taking a 3-1
lead in the fourth. Andruw Jones hit a one-out double, Chipper
Jones walked and Brian Jordan doubled in a run. Galarraga then
drove in a run with a grounder and Wally Joyner followed with an
RBI single.
</P>
<P>
   Baltimore pulled even in the fifth on an RBI single by Albert
Belle and a run-scoring grounder by B.J. Surhoff.
Notes: Baltimore's Delino DeShields recorded his team-high 22nd
stolen base, the first since June 28. ... Atlanta 2B Quilvio Veras
was scratched from the lineup due to illness. He was replaced by
Keith Lockhart. ... Baltimore fell to 23-14 at home. ... Before the
game the Braves activated LHP Mike Remlinger from the disabled list
and designated RHP Dave Stevens for assignment. ... Sanders' 10th
steal in the ninth inning enabled him to reach double figures for
the eighth straight season.
</P>
</TEXT>
